the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret of Maystersparks was born about 1110, in Lewannick, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. She married Thomas de Uppeton in 1129, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1110–":"umbes 1110–Surnud","1101–1140":"1101–1140","1136–Male":"1136–Surnud","1110–Female":"1110–Surnud","       1129":"1129","1136":"1136","1101":"1101","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","about 1110":"umbes 1110","Lewannick, Launceston, Cornwall, England":"Lewannick, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cornwall,England":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Upton, Cornwall, England, UK":"Upton, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1110–":"noin 1110–Kuollut","1101–1140":"1101–1140","1136–Male":"1136–Kuollut","1110–Female":"1110–Kuollut","       1129":"1129","1136":"1136","1101":"1101","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","about 1110":"noin 1110","Lewannick, Launceston, Cornwall, England":"Lewannick, Cornwall, E